theorem Topology.P3_union_of_dense_interior_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : Dense (interior A)) : Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  -- Step 1: `closure (interior A) = univ`.
  have hClIntA : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hA.closure_eq
  -- Step 2: `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
  have hSub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
    have hInner : interior A ⊆ (A ∪ B : Set X) := by
      intro y hy; exact Or.inl hy
    exact closure_mono hInner
  -- Step 3: deduce `closure (A ∪ B) = univ`.
  have hClUnion : closure (A ∪ B) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro y _; simp
    · intro y _
      have : y ∈ closure (interior A) := by
        have : y ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
        simpa [hClIntA] using this
      exact hSub this
  -- Step 4: use the equality of closures to finish.
  have : x ∈ interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
    have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
    simpa [hClUnion, interior_univ] using this
  exact this

theorem Topology.interior_subset_closure_of_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ B) :
    interior A ⊆ closure B := by
  intro x hxInt
  -- From `x ∈ interior A`, we obtain `x ∈ A`.
  have hxA : x ∈ A := interior_subset hxInt
  -- Use the given inclusion `A ⊆ B` to get `x ∈ B`.
  have hxB : x ∈ B := hAB hxA
  -- Every point of `B` lies in `closure B`.
  exact subset_closure hxB
